faqs:
  - title: Where is Miro data stored?
    description: >-
      Under EU Data Center Residency, the compute infrastructure and all
      Customer  Content (production data, backup data and metadata) is hosted
      within the EU  by default. Learn more about Data Center Residency.
  - title: Where can I find information about Miro's uptime and downtimes?
    description: >-
      Check out Miro's Status Page at status.miro.com. This will give you the 
      ability to subscribe for updates, view uptimes, be notified of any
      outages,  and view historical data.
  - title: Do you offer the same level of data protection to all of your users?
    description: >-
      Yes, regardless of which Miro plan rest assured your data is securely
      managed  and held. With TLS 1.2 or higher for transit and AES 256 at rest,
      in compliance  with GDPR and CCPA standards, your data is secured to the
      highest levels at no  additional cost. For advanced security, privacy, and
      administrative controls,  please contact us to learn more about Miro
      Enterprise.
  - title: I found a security bug. Do you have an established bug bounty program?
    description: >-
      Yes, Miro has a bug bounty program on Intigriti. If you'd like to
      participate,  please log in to your Intigriti account and visit the Miro
      Intigriti program page.  Submissions for bounties are handled according to
      the program rules. Please check  the rules carefully before you submit a
      report.
  - title: Can anyone at Miro access my boards?
    description: >-
      No, without your request and permission no one can view your board
      content.  Miro restricts access to the production environment to a limited
      number of  IP addresses and employees.
  - title: Does Miro have an Accessibility Conformance Report (ACR)?
    description: >-
      Refer to Miro's Accessibility Statement and Accessibility Article to learn
      more  about Miro's accessibility features and compliance with
      accessibility standards.
  - title: Where can I find Miro's Terms and Legal documents?
    description: All of Miro's documents can be found at miro.com/legal/terms-of-service/.
  - title: Does Miro use cookies?
    description: >-
      Yes, Miro uses a variety of cookies and similar technologies in our
      Websites  and Services to help us collect Services Data. For more details
      about how we  use these technologies, as well as your opt-out
      opportunities and other options,  please see our Cookie Policy.
  - title: Will Miro offer an API?
    description: >-
      Yes, Please read more to learn about the capabilities of Miro's API at 
      developers.miro.com.
  - title: What controls are in place for Miro AI?
    description: >-
      Learn more about Miro AI security measures, data handling, and compliance 
      through Miro's AI Whitepaper and related documentation.
